result: Canada was colonized starting in the early 16th century. The first European settlement was established by the French explorer Jacques Cartier in 1534, and this marked the beginning of French colonial efforts in Canada. Later, in the early 17th century, Samuel de Champlain founded Quebec City in 1608, solidifying French presence in Canada. Meanwhile, the British also established their own colonies in Canada, with significant colonization beginning in the late 17th and early 18th centuries, particularly with settlements in Nova Scotia and Newfoundland. Canada continued to be a site of competition between French and British forces until British victory in the Seven Years' War (1756–1763), which led to British dominance in the region.
